# Applies to the orchestrator image build (deploy/docker/Dockerfile.orchestrator),
# whose build context is the repo root. The agent image (container/Dockerfile)
# has its own context (./container) and is unaffected by this file.
#
# Goal: ship framework code + runtime assets, NOT local dev state, secrets, or
# anything rebuilt inside the image.

# Rebuilt inside the image (npm ci) — never ship the host's (arm64 on macOS)
# node_modules or the agent-runner's local install.
node_modules
container/agent-runner/node_modules
**/node_modules

# Compiled output is regenerated by the build stage.
dist

# Secrets and local env — credentials reach the orchestrator via env/Secret.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Tenant/org runtime state is mounted from a PVC/hostPath, never baked.
# profiles/example IS kept — it's the copy-me template a new operator starts
# from (referenced by docs/NEW-ORG-GUIDE.md). Real org profiles are gitignored
# and would not be in the context anyway. The `!` re-includes the example dir
# and its contents after the broad exclude.
profiles/*
!profiles/example
!profiles/example/**
# Legacy root-level runtime state (dev single-tenant layout).
store
data
groups

# VCS, CI, and editor cruft.
.git
.github
.gitignore
.husky
*.log

# Tests and coverage — not needed at runtime (source .test.ts files live under
# src/ and are excluded from the compiled dist by tsc anyway; drop them from the
# context to keep the build lean).
**/*.test.ts
coverage
.nyc_output

# Docs-site / marketing assets not read at runtime.
site
assets
kb-ui/node_modules

# OS junk.
.DS_Store
